Requirements:
Beginning with the Fall 2021 term, MTSU will be test-optional for students with a 3.0+ GPA. High school GPA is based on a regular 4.00 scale. To be considered for admission, you must meet one of the following:

A minimum 3.0 high school GPA OR;
A minimum 2.7 high school GPA with a minimum 19 ACT or 990 SAT score (see concordance tables for new SAT scores) OR;
An ACT composite score of 22 or higher (or SAT equivalent) regardless of high school GPA.

Admission to the M.S. in Geosciences program requires the following:
1. an earned bachelor's degree from an accredited university or college;
2. a major in geology/geoscience or one of the cognate sciences (e.g. chemistry, physics, biology, mathematics);
3. an undergraduate GPA of 2.75 or higher on a 4.0 scale;
4. three letters of recommendation;
5. a statement of purpose.
